---
date added: 2026-03-05
title: Pullman Loaf (Pain de Mie)
author: Donna Currie
source: https://www.seriouseats.com/bread-baking-pullman-loaf-recipe
tags: bread, sandwich, yeast
servings: 14
active time: 25 minutes
time required: 2 hours 55 minutes
---

In the bowl of your #stand mixer{}, combine @lukewarm water{1 1/2%cups}, @semolina flour{1%cup}, @honey{2%tablespoons}, @instant yeast{2 1/4%teaspoons}, and @bread flour{2%cups}. Stir to combine. Cover and set aside for ~{20%minutes}.

Add @white wheat flour{1/2%cup}, @salt{1 1/2%teaspoons}, and @butter{3%tablespoons} and knead with the dough hook attachment of your stand mixer until the dough is smooth and elastic. Flour your work surface lightly, and knead by hand briefly, then form the dough into a ball. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and return it to the bowl. Cover with plastic wrap and set aside for ~{30%minutes}.

Preheat the oven to 350°F. Turn out the dough and knead it briefly to knock out the large bubbles. Form it into a log about 13 inches long to fit inside the #pullman loaf pan{}. Place the log in the pan, seam-side down. Put the lid on the pan and set aside until the dough has risen to within about an inch of the top of the pan, at least ~{30%minutes} and up to ~{1 1/2%hours}.

Bake until the loaf is golden brown, about ~{40%minutes}. Remove the loaf from the pan and allow it to cool completely on a #rack{} before slicing.
